===Etymology===
See [[alive]]

====Adjective====
'''live''' (''no {{compar}} or {{superl}}; used only attributively: see usage notes'')

Having life.
:''The post office will not ship live animals.''

A hazardous item
#(''of firearms or explosives'') Capable of causing harm.
#:''The air force practices dropping live bombs on the uninhabited island.''
#(''electric circuit'') charged; energized; usually denoting that the item may cause electrocution if touched.
#:''Use caution when working near live wires.''

====Usage notes====
*'''Live''' in the sense of "having life" is used only attributively (before a noun).  Predicatively (after the noun), '''alive''' is used.  '''Living''' may be used either attributively or predicatively.
**''live animals''; ''these animals are alive''

